<head>
    <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" />
    <title>Create a Circle</title>
    <style>
        .circle{
            width: 100px;
            height: 100px;
            border-radius: 50%;
            background-color: red;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="circle">
    </div>
</body>
</html>

# Note
## If you use px values instead, the radius will be fixed (e.g., border-radius: 50px), and it may not create a circle unless the width and height are exactly equal. Using percentage values ensures proportional rounding regardless of the element's size.
